From: Joe Perches <joe@perches.com>
Date: Tue, 1 Oct 2013 19:04:40 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 16/26] net:drivers/net: Miscellaneous conversions to ETH_ALEN
Patch-mainline: v3.13-rc1

Git-commit: d458cdf712e0c671e8e819abb16ecd6e44f9daec (partial)
References: bsc#909368 FATE#317537


Convert the memset/memcpy uses of 6 to ETH_ALEN
where appropriate.

Also convert some struct definitions and u8 array
declarations of [6] to ETH_ALEN.

Signed-off-by: Joe Perches <joe@perches.com>
Acked-by: Arend van Spriel <arend@broadcom.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Cho, Yu-Chen <acho@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/cnic.c |    4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/cnic.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/cnic.c
@@ -393,7 +393,7 @@ static int cnic_iscsi_nl_msg_recv(struct
 
 			csk->vlan_id = path_resp->vlan_id;
 
-			memcpy(csk->ha, path_resp->mac_addr, 6);
+			memcpy(csk->ha, path_resp->mac_addr, ETH_ALEN);
 			if (test_bit(SK_F_IPV6, &csk->flags))
 				memcpy(&csk->src_ip[0], &path_resp->src.v6_addr,
 				       sizeof(struct in6_addr));
@@ -5565,7 +5565,7 @@ static struct cnic_dev *init_bnx2x_cnic(
 	if (cdev->max_fcoe_conn > BNX2X_FCOE_NUM_CONNECTIONS)
 		cdev->max_fcoe_conn = BNX2X_FCOE_NUM_CONNECTIONS;
 
-	memcpy(cdev->mac_addr, ethdev->iscsi_mac, 6);
+	memcpy(cdev->mac_addr, ethdev->iscsi_mac, ETH_ALEN);
 
 	cp->cnic_ops = &cnic_bnx2x_ops;
 	cp->start_hw = cnic_start_bnx2x_hw;
